Author: Steven Kreitzer <skre@skre.me>
Date:   Mon Dec 18 14:20:59 2023 -0600

Apple NVMe drives are extremely slow when it comes to fsync and fdatasync.
This disables those calls, which will speed up many latency-sensative applications.
This is not safe unless you have some power-loss protection against your storage devices.

Signed-off-by: Steven Kreitzer <skre@skre.me>

diff --git a/fs/sync.c b/fs/sync.c
index dc725914e1ed..f78ad028ac87 100644
--- a/fs/sync.c
+++ b/fs/sync.c
@@ -217,11 +217,15 @@ static int do_fsync(unsigned int fd, int datasync)

 SYSCALL_DEFINE1(fsync, unsigned int, fd)
 {
+	if (unlikely(laptop_mode))
+		return 0;
 	return do_fsync(fd, 0);
 }

 SYSCALL_DEFINE1(fdatasync, unsigned int, fd)
 {
+	if (unlikely(laptop_mode))
+		return 0;
 	return do_fsync(fd, 1);
 }

